in traits about those speakers. Those traits include things such as intelligence, appearance, confidence, character, etc. The key part of the technique revolves around the fact that the recordings the participants listen to are actually produced by one speaker (a bilingual individual) and leads those participants to reach (oftentimes) different conclusions about the same speaker based on language. %0a%3c %0a%3c Ethical objections to the Matched-Guise test have been long documented (specifically with the possible lack of informed consent) and contain limitations affected by the quality and performance of different dialects by the same individual, and how that is received by the listener. %0a%3c %0a%3c https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matched-guise_test#Ethical_unacceptability%0a%3c https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sociolinguistics#Applications%0a%3c https://www.cambridge.org/core/books/abs/research-methods-in-language-attitudes/matchedguise-technique/91729A40F9D2F2DA0F7B22DE61D3244B%0a%3c https://eric.ed.gov/?id=ED367168%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!Change article category%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:Section: E:)%0a%3c (:Category: Varia:)%0a%3c (:Title: The Matched-guise test :)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
